'Dutchess County' is a county located in the U.S. state of New York, in the
state's Mid-Hudson Region of the Hudson Valley. The 2010 census lists the
population as 297,488. The county seat is Poughkeepsie.

Dutchess County is part of the Poughkeepsie–Newburgh–Middletown, NY
Metropolitan Statistical Area as well as the larger New
York–Newark–Bridgeport, NY-NJ-CT-PA Combined Statistical Area.
